# Lovable Backend — Not the AI Agent

This repository is the **backend application** for the Secure SoR app. It is **created from and for the [Lovable.ai](https://lovable.ai) UI**. The **AI Agent** (Boundary, Data Readiness, etc.) is a **separate project** (e.g. in `Documents/AI Agents/agent`) and is applied on top of this backend; it does not live in this repo.

## Authority

- **Master architecture:** `Secure_Canonical_v5.md` — single source of truth for product definition, principles, domain model, and APIs.
- **Detailed specs:** `docs/` — data models (`docs/data-model/`), architecture (`docs/architecture/`), modules (`docs/modules/`).

## Principles (from canonical)

1. **Single Source of Truth** — All sustainability data in structured datasets.
2. **Separation of concerns** — Data layer, reporting layer, AI layer distinct.
3. **No hardcoded report data** — Reports consume structured datasets only.
4. **Evidence centralisation** — Evidence on Data Library records, not reports.
5. **Audit traceability** — Append-only mutation logs.
6. **Explicit boundary model** — Reporting boundary at account level (`account.reportingBoundary`).

## When adding or changing code

- Align with types and structures in `Secure_Canonical_v5.md` (Account, Property, Space, System, DataLibraryRecord, Reporting Boundary, etc.).
- Use `docs/data-model/` and `docs/architecture/` for detailed field and behaviour rules.
- This backend is consumed by the Lovable frontend; ensure endpoints and payloads match what the frontend expects.
- The Data Readiness / Boundary agent is a separate service (different repo); this backend may be called by Lovable alongside that agent.

